.TH sdrdab-decoder 1 "RTL stick compatible application"

.SH NAME sdrdab-decoder \- Sdrdab example Cli


.SH DESCRIPTION
sdrdab-cli is an exemplary application of sdrdab. You can try it out even without the RTL stick - just supply an input file.

This application shows how sdrdab can be used. It allows user to decode DAB/DAB+ signal either from RTL2832U tuner or from raw samples file. Audio stream can be played immediately on speakers and/or saved to file.


.SH SYNOPSIS
Usage: sdrdab-cli [OPTION...] 
  or:  sdrdab-cli [OPTION...] -l	list available devices
  or:  sdrdab-cli [OPTION...] [-t[TUNER_NO=0]]	use n-th tuner
  or:  sdrdab-cli [OPTION...] --open-file=FILENAME	read samples from FILENAME
  or:  sdrdab-cli [OPTION...] [-s] -o OUTPUT	save audio to OUPUT

.SH OPTIONS
 Core radio options:
  -c, --channel=CHANN          Optionally start decoding specified channel instead of the first one. This requires a number, not name
  -f, --frequency=FREQ         Carrier frequency in kHz. Default value: 229072 (DAB+ in Krakow)
                               
 Input options:                
  -l, --list-devices           Lists all available supported tuners and exits
      --open-file=FILENAME     Use FILENAME as input source
  -t, --open-tuner[=TUNER_NO]  Use n-th available tuner as input source (by default first tuner is used)
                               
 Output options:               
  -i, --detailed-info          Print verbosely channel information every time ENTER is pressed
  -o, --output=OUTPUT          Save audio to OUTPUT file
  -s, --silent                 Don't play on speakers (applicable in conjunction with -o switch)
                               
 Algorithm options:
      --convolutional=CONVOLUTIONAL
                               Use decoding algorithms: viterbi
      --resampling_fs=RESAMPLING_FS
                               Resampling frequency: sinc_fast, linear or zero-order

 Informative options:          
  -?, --help                   Give help list
      --usage                  Give a short usage message
  -v, --verbose                Verbose
  -V, --version                Print program version

.SH INTERACTIVE
After being started, this program goes into interactive command-line mode. List of supported commands:
  station		Change current station.
  list		Display list of available stations.
  quit		Exit program.
  help		Display help message.
  license		Display license information.
  restart		Restart program.
